rows.title: Solo Leveling the Cyoa
rows.titleText: This is my first go at making an interactive cyoa.  I was gonna make it 2 point types but the cyoa creator gives me headaches because of how much it confuses me.  If you want to customize your body go do LordValmars Hearth and Body Meta.

rows.title: You
rows.titleText:
There are a few styles authors use to offer this section. From different rows for height, age, race, gender, sex, hair color, eye color... There are many ways to handle this. Personally I prefer to keep things simple.

I also would not include Row Text for this row.

objects.title: Insert
objects.text: You will awaken in your new body at your selected age with memories and history that correspond with your choices.

objects.title: Drop-In
objects.text: You will be dropped into the world in a new body with no history or memories of living in this world prior.

objects.title: Young
objects.text: You start off as a young kid no older than 12.

objects.title: Teen
objects.text: You start off as a teenager between the ages 13 and 17.

objects.title: Adult
objects.text: You start off as an adult, no younger than 18.

objects.title: Human
objects.text: This makes you a normal human. which isn't quite so normal with gates spawning everywhere.

objects.title: Monster
objects.text: This is any non sentient species that spawns from dungeons.  Just know you probably wont last long with Sung Jinwoo hunting monsters left and right.

objects.title: Other
objects.text: This is any sentient race that isn't human.  This includes Dwarfs, Snow elves, Demons, Dragons, Beastmen, Monstrous Humanoids, Giants, Insectoids, and Demonic Specters.

rows.title: Locations
rows.titleText: This is where you choose to start.

objects.title: Earth
objects.text: This is anywhere on Earth.  You should know that the plot only touches on Korea, Japan, USA, and China.  Most of the plot takes place in Korea.

objects.title: Gates
objects.text: This is within any Gate.  if you choose a Gate that has already broken free or hasn't been created yet, you are instead sent to a random working Gate.

objects.title: Dungeons
objects.text: Dungeons are only created by Sung Jinwoo's system.  So you are probably stuck until he gets it and enters the dungeon.

objects.title: Other
objects.text: This is any other place not mentioned in the other options.  This includes the moon, saturn, and the sun.

objects.title: Before God's Death
objects.text: This is any time before God died.  Yes, big G is dead and his children are coming to earth.

objects.title: Before Solo Leveling
objects.text: This is any time before the start of Solo Leveling.  We never get any real dates so you might have to just guess.

objects.title: Solo Leveling
objects.text: This is the start of Solo Leveling.  You have days before Sung Jinwoo gets his system and starts his climb to the top.

objects.title: Solo Leveling Ragnarok
objects.text: This is after Solo Leveling when Sung Jinwoo is out fighting other big G's to protect earth.  His kid just got his own system and is supposed to be pretty talented.

rows.title: Power Level
rows.titleText: This is how strong the world is and how strong people can get.  This affects your allies, enemies, and yourself.  Just know a weakened God is still a God.

objects.text: This world is made of paper and so are you.
This is a weaker world and it makes for weaker people.

objects.title: Normal
objects.text: This is the normal Solo Leveling experience.
This is a tougher world and it makes for tougher people.
This is a world ruled by power.  Don't lose yourself to the thrill.

rows.title: Size
rows.titleText: This decides how big you want the world to be.  Do you want your own little multiverse or maybe you just earth with no other planets.

objects.title: Finite
objects.text: This makes it so your whole universe is just the milky way.  You might get cramps from how small it is.

objects.title: Small
objects.text: This makes your home universe about half as big as our universe

objects.title: Average
objects.text: This is make your home universe about as big as our universe

objects.title: Infinite
objects.text: This makes your home universe infinite in size.  The other God's might get jealouse

objects.title: Novel
objects.text: This makes it so the world is the one based on the novel

objects.title: Webtoon
objects.text: This makes it so the world is the one based off the webtoon.

objects.title: Game
objects.text: This makes it so the world is the one based off the mobile game.

objects.title: Anime
objects.text: This makes it so the world is the one based off the anime.

objects.title: Custom
objects.text: This makes it so the world is based off some other form of media.  Want a realistic looking world or people that look like One Piece characters.

rows.title: Openness
rows.titleText: This is where you decide how open your universe is.

objects.title: Normal
objects.text: Your home universe is just as open as the original Solo Leveling universe.  This makes it so Solo Leveling Ragnarok happens normally.

objects.title: Connected
objects.text: This makes it so instead of other realities joining in on your fun they are instead just really far away in your home universe.  This makes Solo Leveling Ragnarok a little awkward due to the Gods also being Natives instead of invaders.

objects.title: Closed Off
objects.text: This makes it so no one from outside your universe can interfere in yours.  This will make it so Solo Leveling Ragnarok never happens.

objects.title: Fully Open
objects.text: This makes your universe completely open.  Anyone who trips wrong could enter your universe on accident.  This makes gates more prominent and invites more gods to interfere in Solo Leveling Ragnarok.

rows.title: Drawbacks
rows.titleText: This is where you choose drawbacks to gain some points.  There are 2 types of drawbacks.  Personal and Global.  Personal Drawbacks only affect you and Global Drawbacks affect everybody.

objects.title: Monster Bait
objects.text: This makes monsters more aggressive towards you.  If you are a monster then it makes sentient species more aggressive towards you.

objects.title: Displaced Gear
objects.text: This makes it so all your items are now hidden in random Gates.  You will know which Gates have your stuff.  if the Gate is closed before you get your gear, another random gate will appear with your stuff in it.  only you can find your stuff in these Gates.

objects.title: No talent.
objects.text: This makes it so the first time you ever get appraised for a hunters license you will appear as the lowest possible rank that still qualifies to be a hunter.

objects.title: Family Man
objects.text: This makes it so you have to take care of a younger relative of yours.  Luckily they are almost 18 so you only need to take care of them for a maximum of 2 years.

objects.title: Sung Jin Who?
objects.text: This makes it so Sung Jinwoo dies in the double gate that would have given him his system.  Now you have to save the world and deal with an evil Architect.

objects.title: More Monarchs
objects.text: This makes it so there are more Monarchs.  Just know each Monarch is considered a bigger threat than multiple nuclear bombs and they killed their own God.

objects.title: Godly Attention
objects.text: This makes it so God's now think you are extra special.  Just know these God's don't like to share and if they can't have you, no one can have you.

objects.title: Worse Gates
objects.text: This makes it so all Gates are a grade higher in danger and appear twice as frequently.

rows.title: Gear
rows.titleText: This section is where you buy gear and pets.

objects.title: ID
objects.text: This is a basic ID that automatically changes itself with up to date information about you.  It also combines with any other form of identification you own.

objects.title: Porter's Bag
objects.text: This is a backpack that is 10 time bigger on the inside than normal.

objects.title: Starter Kit
objects.text: This is a basic kit for beginner hunters.  It includes a basic weapon of your choice and some basic leather armor.

objects.title: Baby Animal
objects.text: This is a baby version of any mundane animal.  If you raise it right you could have a friend for life.

objects.title: Rations
objects.text: This is a lunchbox that always refills at lunch time with the food you crave most.

objects.title: Your own Guild
objects.text: This is a custom made building built to house your future guild.  It is by the code and you don't need to pay for the amenities.

objects.title: S Class Kit
objects.text: This includes a master work weapon of your choice and armor custom fitted to match your fighting style.

objects.title: Cornicopia
objects.text: This is the Cornucopia of myth.  It endlessly spawns any food or drink you want.  You could end world hunger or kill someone with bread.

objects.title: Baby Monster
objects.text: This is a baby version of whatever monster you want.  If you raise it right you could get a useful ally.

objects.title: Sung Jinwoo's Compass
objects.text: You get a compass that always points towards what you need most.

rows.title: Gear [with Freebies]
rows.titleText: This is the section typically used to offer items or gear. This example is a gear section that allows the player to choose a set number of items or gear for free. In this example, only gear priced at 5 points is offered free. If you have gear choices with varying prices it can be tricky to offer freebies otherwise. In this example 3 freebies are allowed. You can increase this number in [Open Features] - [Manage Points] - [Gear: Starting Sum]. You can also make the free gear points be visible in the point bar if you remove the "hidden" part in the "Id Needed to Show" box of the point management. Or, alternatively, you can make it only show up when you have opened the Gear tab, same as this section, by changing "hidden" to "tab-gear".

objects.title: Gear 1
objects.text:
How am I doing this? In the Scores I have set two Scores. One for 5 points, and one for 1 Gear point. 

These two scores have requirements attached for "Equal to" and "More Than", but linked to your current "Gear" point.

What this means is that if you have any "Gear" points, or "More than 0", selecting this use 1 Gear point.

Furthermore if your Gear points "equal to 0" it will instead cost you 5 points.

This has the effect of allowing you to choose however many "Gear points" you have set as freebies.

objects.title: Gear 6
objects.text: This is an example of a gear or item that costs 10 points.

rows.title: Talents
rows.titleText: This is where you can purchase talents that may make your life easier.

objects.title: Fighting
objects.text: Choose a weapon or fighting style.  You now have an immense talent for it alongside a general aptitude for combat.

objects.title: Crafting
objects.text: Choose a form of crafting.  you now have an immense talent for it and a passable talent at any artistic endeavor.

objects.title: Leadership
objects.text: You are a natural leader.  You have the charisma of a maxed out fallout character and the abilities to actually make use of your allies.

objects.title: Caretaker
objects.text: You have a natural talent at taking care of others.  It doesn't matter if they are a baby animal or a random child that got lost.  You just get what they need and can foster a feeling of family incredibly quickly.

rows.title: Powers
rows.titleText: This is where you will purchase your powers.  Make sure you can actually use them before you choose which ones you want.

objects.title: A Rank
objects.text: You are now guaranteed to awaken an ability with the potential to reach at least A rank.  It could still be any abiliy but it has potential.

objects.title: Random
objects.text: Go to the super power wiki and roll for a single random power.  You don't get any of the secondary powers if your power doesn't come with it.

objects.title: Devil Fruit
objects.text: Choose any Devil Fruit that isn't a logia or mythical zoan.  You now have it and its weaknesses.

objects.title: Secondary Powers
objects.text: You now have all the secondary powers you would need to actually fight at the God level in this universe.  No breaking all the bones in your body due to your muscles being too strong.

objects.title: Better Random
objects.text: Go to the super power wiki and roll for 3 random powers.  you now have them.  you don't get any of the secondary powers if your power doesn't come with it.

objects.title: Monarch
objects.text: Choose a Monarch from the wiki.  You now have a system similar to Sung Jinwoo's that bestows upon you the power of said Monarch.  Just remember the Monarchs all have different specialties and the only reason Sung Jinwoo won originally was due to it being a battle of attrition.

objects.title: Magic
objects.text: Choose a magic system from any work of fiction.  You now have an average amount of talent in it.  This doesn't introduce the energy you use it for into the world so be careful in which magic system you choose.  You also have to figure out how to use said magic by yourself.

objects.title: Tinker
objects.text: Choose a world.  You now have all the blueprints for everything that world has ever made.  This does not come with the materials so make sure you can actually use the blueprints.

rows.title: Boons
rows.titleText: These are some boons you can get to help yourself survive in this universe.

objects.title: Iron Will
objects.text: This boon gives you the ability to walk towards death everyday and not struggle with anxiety in combat. Just know Sung Jinwoo did this for years on end with no hope of actually getting stronger.

objects.title: Pinnacle
objects.text: This boon keeps you in the best shape possible, no matter what you eat or do.  Being a hunter is a very physically taxing job.

objects.title: Sanity
objects.text: This boon makes it so you will always recover from any mental issues.  Being a hunter is very taxing on the mind.  Especially when your friends die around you.

objects.title: Immunity
objects.text: This boon gives you all the immunities you need.  No one can steal your powers, see your future, alter your timeline, or reality warp you away.  The God's wont be happy about this boon.

objects.title: Credits
objects.text: I really want to thank the solo leveling wiki for all its information and LordValmar for his template.  I tried the discord server link on his website but it didn't work so I'm thanking him here.
